<p>First question: For pre-blocking gauge, I counted the number of stitches=
 and rows in a 4=E2=80=B3 square.  Is it possible to have knitted a 16=C3=
=9720 swatch when Patons says that a #7 needle would be 20=C3=9728?</p>
<p>Second question.  How do I know what size to block the swatch?  I got ov=
erzealous and knitted a 8=E2=80=B3 x 9=E2=80=B3 swatch.  Is that what I blo=
ck it to?</p>
<p>Thank you so much!</p>
<p>Elaine<br>
Greensboro, NC</p>
