                <br>
                <small class=3D"comment-time">
                    November 9, 2020                    @
        2:06 am                </small>
            </p>
            <div class=3D"commententry">
                            <p>Hi! I think it=E2=80=99s probably best to ma=
ke a stockinette hat (and block it) to check your stockinette gauge in the =
round, because this will be more relevant for the Trek sweater fit. Or you =
could start with a sleeve, and use that as a swatch =E2=80=93 we=E2=80=99ve=
 got a tutorial on that here: <a href=3D"https://blog.tincanknits.com/2017/=
03/02/the-sleeve-swatch/" rel=3D"ugc">https://blog.tincanknits.com/2017/03/=
02/the-sleeve-swatch/</a> .  If you are getting too 23.5 sts in 4 inches ra=
ther than 22, you need to try a LARGER needle size, not a smaller one, beca=
use your stitches are too small (that=E2=80=99s why you have more in 4=E2=
=80=B3). If it were me, I=E2=80=99d try going up a single needle size, but =
you may require two sizes change to get to 22, it=E2=80=99s impossible to k=
now until you try.  Best luck! ~ Em</p>
            </div>
